Last Broadcast Date: Wed 13 Jul 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the Indian seaman reunited with his family after 11 months as a hostage of Somali pirates. Also, the dangerous world of dating in Tehran, explored by British/Iranian writer Kamin Mohammadi. And the glories of an Englishman's shed - Jon Earl tells us how he records entire bands in his small garden shed. Show less